    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-29T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/971.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Germany</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-29T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 26, 1 p.m., via London. German minister at Peking instructed that if
                    the other powers do not consent to loan without insisting on conditions of
                    foreign control of its expenditure he is to conform. German Government will
                    support no further advances unless the Chinese accept the conditions of
                    control.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leishman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
